begin_memory_text: We talked about ourselves, our names, where we were from. We also talked about employment and COVID-19, and how that had affected our lives as far as school and work. I shared that my brother used to live in the town that my partner lives in now, so we talked about that city for a bit.
middle_memory_text: Around the middle, I believe we talked about video games and video game development. We are both interested in video games, so we talked about what we played and what we were looking forward to coming out. We talked about negative things in the gaming industry as well.
end_memory_text: We talked about our interests in music, and concerts we had been to. I mentioned some electronic bands that they might like because they mentioned they liked electronic music. We talked about heavy metal and our interests in that genre, as well as concerts we had been to of the genre.
rest_of_day_open: The rest of my week will likely be relaxed, since today is Thursday. Tomorrow is Friday, so I will likely see some friends and hang out with them. On Saturday, I plan to go hiking by myself, which I am looking forward to. I find that being outdoors alone is good for my mental health. On Sunday I will likely do some homework.
critical_positive: Something that went well for our conversation was our many shared interests, such as video games and music. It made it so we could have something in common, and made the conversation more comfortable. We were able to share recommendations for things that we were interested in, knowing that the other may be interested in it as well.
critical_negative: I can't really say that anything about the conversation was bad. My partner was easy to talk to and didn't shy away from any questions, and gave full answers as well. One issue I guess would be that I accidentally spoke over him, but I stopped, apologized, and allowed him to finish his thought.

begin_memory_text: We exchanged our first name. We talked about where we live, what we do and how COVID-19 affected our lives. He goes to a university in Kentucky and luckily was largely unaffected by the pandemic.
middle_memory_text: We talked about video games and computer stuff. I tried to diagnose why his system died and probably wasn't much help. We talked about what video games we have played and early access and preordering video games and consoles.
end_memory_text: We shared musical interests and talked a lot about metal genres and bands and past experience going to shows and festivals. We exchanged bands to listen to later.
rest_of_day_open: Tomorrow might be tough. It will be the first day that I spend the most of taking calls in a call center. I really have no idea what to expect from customers calling in. The weekend should be good, though I need to do some rearranging and grocery shopping. So I won't be able to relax as much as I would like.
critical_positive: We had a lot of stuff in common that we could play off of and talk about it. We both are into computers, video games, and some metal and electronic music genres. There were no real significant gaps in the conversation but I felt like I probably carried most of it.
critical_negative: I could tell that we are both naturally fairly awkward and introverted. I have a lot of experience with talking to people despite that so I was able to drive the conversation past that hurdle. He seemed a little more hesitant to talk at first than I was, but other than that I think the conversation went really well.
